NUMBER 112
NAME Grymwood, entrance
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Standing on a mound of dirt, you view the world around you. A wall of trees stretches as far as you can see, climbing into the Teeth of Shartan in the distant north. At first glance, the forest looks to be an impenetrable barrier of twisted branches and newly awakend greenery growing like mad, but footprints in the soft earth say otherwise.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 115
EXIT S 560
EXIT ABOVE 2141
IFVERB RECALL -1
	IFVAR SKILL32 >= 3
		ECHO PLAYER Grymwood is reputed to be enchanted by children who died before their time.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
FOREST
DAY_LIGHT
;
NUMBER 110
NAME Grymwood, Matriarch Tree
MONSTER_GROUP 10
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Suddenly the undergrowth clears and you find yourself at the base of an enormous tree. Its red, brown, fibrous trunk is easily as wide as a house. It grows straight up and out of sight above the canopy. Mighty branches sprout regularly from its sides. Gnarled roots dig into the ground like giant fingers. A few persistent snow patches dot the surface of nearly decomposed needle-like leaves. There appears to be a small opening at the base of the trunk.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 111
EXIT NE 117
ITEM 0 72 ADJ1=294 VAL2=109
IFVERB RECALL -1
	IFVAR SKILL32 >= 5
		ECHO PLAYER This giant post-cataclysmic redwood tree was the hideout of Vashaska, reputed consort of Dahkahn, and a powerful, evil necromancer in her own right. If you recall the story correctly, she agreed to execute her own children as the price for power. Dahkahn grew weary of her anyway and slew her for his amusement one night. Ironically, her soul remains trapped in this great tree, the Matriarch Tree: mother of all the other trees in the forest.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
FOREST
DAY_LIGHT
;
NUMBER 111
NAME Grymwood, rubber plants
MONSTER_GROUP 10
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The undergrowth is robust here. Big plants, with huge rubbery leaves, crowd out the other vegitation. Large buds have formed on the branches at the base of last years leaves, and will push them off the plant as they mature. As you push the plants aside to pass, the branches spring back into place, giving you a good swat on the behind. Every time this happens, you get the feeling that someone is laughing.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 110
EXIT E 115
EXIT SW 3003
IFVERB RECALL -1
	IFVAR SKILL32 >= 5
		ECHO PLAYER The spirit of Vashaska's son is said to live in these plants. That is why they are so robust: they are still filled with little boy spunk.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
FOREST
DAY_LIGHT
;
NUMBER 113
NAME Grymwood, dry bed
MONSTER_GROUP 10
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The trail follows a stony, dry stream bed. On either side, banks of new yellow flowers burst through the ground, creating the impression of a magical golden path curving gently through the trees. A delicate breeze causes the flowers to curtsy toward you with petals fluttering, giving you the impression that someone is giggling.
*DESCRIPTION_END
