MONSTER_GROUP 10
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The air feels dense here and seems to muffle all sounds so that the only ones you can hear are your own. Thick old trees with gnarled trunks stand like solemn sentries, unmindful of the gay chatter of birds and squirrels that fills the rest of the forest. Are they watching you? Surely it is merely a trick of the light.
*DESCRIPTION_END
