*DESCRIPTION_START
Small pines find precarious footing in the rock outcroppings of these foothills. A stream bound for the Eltinmar spurts out from between two boulders. The water, unlocked from ice, leaps through crannies in the sheer rock face and collects in a round granite basin surrounded by the tracks of small animals. Occasionally a squirrel sprints along the branches from one tree to the next carrying new soft leaves in its mouth.
*DESCRIPTION_END

