NUMBER 716
NAME Teeth of Shartan, landslide
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A deep pile of snow still remains piled deep against the shady side of the tons of rock and rubble which bury the road here. Bits of cloth and metal beneath the landslide seem to suggest that this spot may have been the end for a previous adventuring party. A path leads eastward through the scattered rock and debris, and the road continues more or less unimpeded to the north.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 27
EXIT E 715
EXIT N 717
EXIT ABOVE 4
;
;
NUMBER 717
NAME Teeth of Shartan, Valley Road
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The stream side path runs north-south here, and is in remarkably good repair. Fine stonework lines the sides of the road, and the surface itself is paved in smooth, flat rocks from the streambed. Who would have built such a fine road in such a remote location is hard to fathom. Although most of the winter snow has melted from the sun-warmed stones of the road, the track that leads southeast through scattered uquart trees is still hidden beneath the snow.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 28
EXIT S 716
EXIT SE 715
EXIT ABOVE 4
EXIT N 718
;
NUMBER 718
NAME Teeth of Shartan, Valley Road
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A rocky promontory looms over the road to the west, its nearly vertical sides throttling the valley. Thin channels of melting snow from the slope have washed away some of the soil beneath the road, carrying it towards the mountain stream. A few scattered uquart dot the rocky slopes, but they are thin and sickly compared to those in the grove below. Loose stones and other debris cover what is left of the road, which, despite its fine craftsmanship, is gradually succumbing to the ravages of time and weather.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 28
EXIT ABOVE 4
EXIT S 717
EXIT NE 719
;
NUMBER 719
NAME Teeth of Shartan, west of bridge
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The valley closes down around the stream here, becoming not so much a valley as a narrow gorge through the rocks. The mountain stream, fed by the melting snow of the upper slopes, tumbles through the pass with a thunderous roar. An ancient bridge of rough-hewn uquart logs spans the stream, allowing passage to the other side.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 28
EXIT ABOVE 4
EXIT SW 718
;
ITEM 0 608 VAL2=720
;
NUMBER 720
NAME Teeth of Shartan, bridge
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Well aged uquart logs lashed together with stout rope form this sturdy bridge accross the stream. The builder of this bridge clearly knew his craft well, for despite its considerable age, the bridge is still quite sound. Upstream, the swollen stream flows in a great cataract down the steep incline of a narrow raceway and over a magnificent formation of ice and water. To the east there lies a small stand of stunted uquart, and to the west, a road leads down the valley.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 27
EXIT ABOVE 4
EXIT W 719
EXIT E 721
;
NUMBER 721
NAME Teeth of Shartan, foundation
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A few small, gnarled uquart trees stand sparsely about this small hollow, which is surrounded on three sides by towering cliffs. A large rectangle of carefully shaped rocks is set in the ground here, and in its midst stands the dilapidated ruin of an ancient stone hearth. Although perhaps it was once home to a trapper or miner, the hearth now shelters only a solitary chipmunk, who scurries in an out of its many openings. A sturdy bridge of lashed uquart logs crosses to the other bank.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 27
EXIT S 722
EXIT N 732
