NUMBER 722
NAME Teeth of Shartan, rocky bank
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A narrow rocky bank separates the steep mountainside and the swift stream here, providing a natural passage to the north and south. This side of the stream is strewn with many small stones, worn smooth and round by the flowing waters. Strong currents and waves from the stream curl douse the rocks with frigid snowmelt, making the footing here slick at best.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 27
EXIT N 721
EXIT SW 723
;
NUMBER 723
NAME Teeth of Shartan, rocky bank
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A small creek trickles out from a dark opening in the rock face here, its water steaming in the cool mountain air. A few of the smooth streambed stones have been deliberately placed in a circle around the creek to collect its waters in a still pool before they join the rushing torrent of the mountain stream.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 27
EXIT NE 722
EXIT SW 724
