NUMBER 724
NAME Teeth of Shartan, Rocky Bank
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A titanic wall of rock rises from the streambed to the lofty peaks, diverting the turbulent flow of water around it. Upstream, a bank of worn streambed rocks, pushed by eons of flowing water, has piled up behind the obstruction,forming a beach that attracts no bathers. The swollen stream has covered over most of the beach, however, leaving only a small strip between the water's edge and the cliff behind.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 723
;
NUMBER 730
NAME Teeth of Shartan, avalanche chute
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A loose pile of rocks and other debris has accumulated a the base of this nearly vertical avalance chute, which rises to the top of the mountains high overhead. Snow, ice and rock constantly fall from the unstable slope. The continuous pumelling from above has fractured and broken the rocks until a deep crevice has been carved into the mountainside.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DAY_LIGHT
MOUNTAIN
;
ITEM 0 63 ADJ1=91 VAL2=729
;ITEM 0 is a deep crevice -- a portal to room 729
;
ITEM 1 213 ADJ1=490 ADJ2=462 VAL2=731
;ITEM 1 is rubble --- climbable portal to 731
IFENTRY
	RANDOM DUMMY1 1 25 0
	IFVAR DUMMY1 < 6
		RANDOM CHUTEDMG 2 15 0
		PLREVENT 7
		CONTPLREVENT
		DAMAGE CRUSH CHUTEDMG A large rock comes tumbling down the chute!
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 731
NAME Teeth of Shartan, rubble pile
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A massive pile of broken rock and other rubble lies heaped against the
mountain here, the remains of countless past rockslides. A wide chute cut
into the rock above is no doubt the source of the pile. One unfortunate
uquart tree, uprooted by a past slide, has struggled to survive among the
loose rocks and beneath a large boulder despite the unnatural angle of its
trunk. As the winter's snow melts away from its branches, tufts of new
growth have appeared at the tips of its surviving branches, a testament
to the tenacity of the uquart species.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
;
ITEM 0 78 ADJ1=178 VAL2=707
; Item 0 is a large boulder, a climbable portal to room 707
;
ITEM 1 213 VAL2=730
; Item 1 is some rubble, a climblable portal to room 730
;
NUMBER 732
NAME Teeth of Shartan, dam base
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Some unnatural force has confined the wild mountain stream here behind a magnificent earthenwork dam, which spans the wide gap between the slopes of two mountains flanking the valley to the east and west. A few uquart are scattered about this side of the dam, and seem to thrive in its loose soil. Although the winter snow still dusts their branches,they already have started to put out new growth. A steep road leads up the slope of the dam, alongside the torrent of water careening down the spillway.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 26
EXIT ABOVE 4
EXIT S 721
EXIT U 733
;
NUMBER 733
NAME Teeth of Shartan, dam top
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The view from atop this earthenwork dam is breathtaking. Behind the dam, a
lake of deepest blue lies nestled among several rocky peaks, its surface
still a mottle of broken ice and liquid water. Due north, across the lake,
a single peak rises high above all others of the range. At the summit of
this magnificent mountain is a massive formation of broken rocks. Unlike
the majority of the surrounding peaks, this one is more or less flat on
top, almost as if it had been sheared off some distance below its summit
in a cataclysmic event. The road skirts the edge of the lake to the
northwest and northeast.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 26
EXIT ABOVE 4
EXIT D 732
EXIT NW 734
EXIT NE 741
;
NUMBER 734
NAME Teeth of Shartan, Lakeside Road
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This fine road has seen little maintainence in recent times. A great number of rocks and even a few boulders have tumbled down the slopes above and come to rest in the flat of the roadway, and here and there tufts of grass poke through cracks in the surface, struggling to survive in the cold mountain spring. Many more seem to have rolled past the road, for the lake shore below is made up entirely of bits and pieces of broken rock.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 26
EXIT SE 733
EXIT ABOVE 4
EXIT NE 735
;
NUMBER 735
NAME Teeth of Shartan, Lakeside Road
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A narrow stream surges down from the mountain peaks and through a wide metal culvert beneath the road, feeding the waters of the lake below. Despite the obvious age of this construction and the volume of water flowing through it as the mountain snows melt, the road shows no signs of flooding, a testament to its designers.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 26
EXIT ABOVE 4
EXIT SW 734
EXIT E 736
