NUMBER 736
NAME Teeth of Shartan, Lakeside Road
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The high cliff which flanks the road to the north still bears the scars of the effort with which it was excavated. Tiny rivulets of water course down the cliff face at every crack and hole. A short drop to the icy cold water of the lake borders the road on the opposite side. A steep slope still thick with winter snow, rises towards the formation at the mountaintop, known as the Fang of Shartan.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
MONSTER_GROUP 26
EXIT ABOVE 4
EXIT E 737
