CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The pitch of the bank is much shallower here than on the other side of the lake, and a sizeable stand of uquart have taken root in the rich soil at the edge of the lake. The gentle waves of the lake lap at the legs of several weatherbeaten wooden tables. Some large bins, their metal rusted through in spots, have been placed here to help preserve the senic mountain park.
*DESCRIPTION_END
