NUMBER 742
NAME Fang of Shartan, Base
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The slope flattens somewhat here, where the steep mountainside meets the vertical wall of the rock formation known as the Fang of Shartan. A deep snow drift still remains at the base of the rock face from the winter. Loose rock litters the ground here, and two small crosses of wood mark the remains of two previous adventurers who dared to try their luck at climbing the treacherous face. A steep slope leads down to the lakeside road far below.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
;
ITEM 0 611 ADJ1=583 VAL2=736
;
ITEM 1 605 ADJ1=332
IFVERB climb 1
   CLEARVERB
   EQUAL abweafact 0
   IFVAR WEA > 5
      EQUAL abweafact WEA
      MULT abweafact 5
      ECHO PLAYER (The weather conditions make the climb more difficult.)
   ENDIF
   EQUAL abclimbsk skill5
   MULT abclimbsk 5
   RANDOM abclimbroll 1 100 0
   ADD abclimbroll abclimbsk
   SUB abclimbroll abweafact
   IFVAR abclimbroll > 110
	ECHO PLAYER You easily climb the rock face.
	ECHO OTHERS %n easily climbs the rock face.
   	MOVE 743
	AFFECT 743
	ECHO OTHERS %n climbs up to the ledge from the face below.
	AFFECT 742
   ENDIF
   IFVAR abclimbroll < 50
      ECHO PLAYER You suffer an attack of acute anxiety and abort the climb.
      ECHO OTHERS %n starts to climb the face, but cannot.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR abclimbroll > 49
      IFVAR abclimbroll < 111
         ECHO PLAYER You start up the face with care, but slip and fall.
         ECHO OTHERS %n starts up the face with care, but slips and falls.
         DAMAGE CRUSH 20 A dull thud sounds as ground and body meet.
         POSITION LAY
         RANDOM DUMMY1 1 100 0
         ADD DUMMY1 AGI
         IFVAR DUMMY1 < 150
             ECHO PLAYER Your momentum carries you on down the slope.
             ECHO OTHERS %n continues to fall on down the slope.
             MOVE 736
             AFFECT 736
             ECHO OTHERS %n comes tumbling down the slope from above.
             DAMAGE CRUSH 10 A rock finally stops the fall.
         ELSE
             ECHO PLAYER You manage to check your speed and stop.
         ENDIF
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
IFVERB ascend -1
   ECHO PLAYER You fly up to a small ledge in the rock face.
   ECHO OTHERS %n flies up the rock face to a small ledge overhead.
   MOVE 743
   AFFECT 743
   ECHO OTHERS %n flies up to the ledge from the ground below.
   AFFECT 742
ENDIF
;
;
;
NUMBER 743
NAME Fang of Shartan, ledge
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This narrow ledge provides a welcome rest for weary climbers, for although
the climb on the face below is nearly vertical, the rest of the climb is
along an overhang which thrusts outward from the mountain. Although most
of the ice and snow at lower altitudes has melted, winter still holds a
tight grasp on the mountain top. Icicles dangle from overhead ledges,
dripping frigid water down onto the ledge. A narrow crevice in the rock
provides the only purchase in the smooth rock above, and the climb down
the face from here is nearly as difficult.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
;
ITEM 0 605 ADJ1=332
; Item 0 is the scripted rock face leading down
IFVERB climb 0
   CLEARVERB
   EQUAL abweafact 0
   IFVAR WEA > 5
      EQUAL abweafact WEA
      MULT abweafact 5
      ECHO PLAYER (The weather conditions make the climb more difficult.)
   ENDIF
   EQUAL abclimbsk skill5
   MULT abclimbsk 5
   RANDOM abclimbroll 1 100 0
   ADD abclimbroll abclimbsk
   SUB abclimbroll abweafact
   IFVAR abclimbroll > 110
	ECHO PLAYER You easily climb down the rock face.
	ECHO OTHERS %n easily climbs down the rock face.
   	MOVE 742
	AFFECT 742
	ECHO OTHERS %n climbs down the face from the ledge above.
	AFFECT 743
   ENDIF
   IFVAR abclimbroll < 50
      ECHO PLAYER You suffer an attack of acute anxiety and abort the climb.
      ECHO OTHERS %n starts to climb down the face, but cannot.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR abclimbroll > 49
      IFVAR abclimbroll < 111
         ECHO PLAYER You start down the face with care, but slip and fall.
         ECHO OTHERS %n starts down the face with care, but slips and falls.
	 ECHO OTHERS A dull thud sounds as ground and body meet.
         MOVE 742
         AFFECT 742
         ECHO OTHERS %n falls from the ledge above.
         DAMAGE CRUSH 30 A dull thud sounds as ground and body meet.
         POSITION LAY
         RANDOM DUMMY1 1 100 0
	 ADD DUMMY1 AGI
	 IFVAR abcatchroll < 130
             ECHO PLAYER Your momentum carries you on down the slope.
             ECHO OTHERS %n continues to fall on down the slope.
             MOVE 736
             AFFECT 736
             ECHO OTHERS %n comes tumbling down the slope from above.
             DAMAGE CRUSH 10 A rock finally stops the fall.
         ELSE
             ECHO PLAYER You manage to check your speed and stop.
             ECHO OTHERS %n manages to check %h speed and stop.
         ENDIF
         AFFECT 743
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
IFVERB descend -1
   ECHO PLAYER You fly down to the base of the rock face.
   ECHO OTHERS %n flies down to the base of the rock face.
   MOVE 742
   AFFECT 742
   ECHO OTHERS %n flies down from the ledge overhead.
   AFFECT 743
ENDIF
